fix(iter24-p9): register IReadOnlyList<IStrategy> so EngineHostFactory.Create starts

EffectExecutor takes IReadOnlyList<IStrategy>, but both DI composition paths
(AddStrategiesFromOptions used by EngineHostFactory.Create, and AddStrategies
used by the standalone Host) registered strategies only as IEnumerable<IStrategy>.
GetRequiredService<EffectExecutor>() therefore threw at startup (cannot resolve
IReadOnlyList<IStrategy>), failing the engine before it ever connected. This broke
the dashboard backtest path AND every cTrader pipeline test (the "pre-existing"
sim failures).

Now materialize the active strategies once as IReadOnlyList<IStrategy> and resolve
IEnumerable<IStrategy> from the same singleton (one strategy set, both shapes).

Verified by a real run: InProcessCtraderTest (engine <-> NetMQ <-> real cBot in
cTrader's backtester, live EURUSD data) now starts and produces 7 trades over 432
bar evaluations. Was failing at engine startup before this fix.

